        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 4 at 4:13PM MDT by NWS Cheyenne WY</headline>
        <description>At 412 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
McGrew, or 15 miles southeast of Scottsbluff, moving north at 60 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bayard, Minatare, Melbeta, McGrew, Kilpatrick Lake, Chimney Rock
National Historic Site, Lake Minatare State Recreation Area,
Scottsbluff Airport, Wrights Gap, Moomaw Corner, and South Bayard
Junction.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
